481
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:13,601
but I fixed it, so...

482
00:23:13,720 --> 00:23:15,722
You can stop worrying
if everybody at the firm

483
00:23:15,840 --> 00:23:18,650
respects you, because they do.

484
00:23:23,120 --> 00:23:24,531
Everyone except you.

485
00:23:31,440 --> 00:23:33,044
No, Louis, including me.

486
00:23:33,440 --> 00:23:36,489
Listen, I may not like
how you got your name on the wall,

487
00:23:36,640 --> 00:23:38,210
but that doesn't mean
it shouldn't be up there.

488
00:23:40,880 --> 00:23:42,211
Congratulations, Louis.

489
00:23:43,960 --> 00:23:45,007
Thanks, Jeff.

490
00:23:46,640 --> 00:23:48,847
Hey, maybe we can even
get drinks this week.

491
00:23:50,760 --> 00:23:53,650
- Name partner buys.
- Deal.

492
00:23:53,880 --> 00:23:55,006
Done.

493
00:24:01,080 --> 00:24:02,969
You can leave the coffee,
but I'm not getting up.

494
00:24:03,080 --> 00:24:06,448
Mike, you've been working for seven
hours straight. You need a break.

495
00:24:06,560 --> 00:24:08,369
I've been working for seven hours
because if I tell Harvey

496
00:24:08,520 --> 00:24:10,966
what's going on before I have a fix,
he is gonna pull the plug.

497
00:24:11,080 --> 00:24:13,003
Well, then maybe the plug
needs to be pulled.

498
00:24:13,120 --> 00:24:15,805
Rachel, just because Joe Henderson is
a bullshit plaintiff doesn't mean

499
00:24:15,920 --> 00:24:18,685
- they didn't cover things up.
- It doesn't mean that they did.

500
00:24:19,840 --> 00:24:21,080
Okay, fine.

501
00:24:21,200 --> 00:24:23,851
Why would he ask for that report
if he knew it would hurt our case?

502
00:24:25,040 --> 00:24:26,565
- I don't know.
- I don't know either,

503
00:24:26,680 --> 00:24:28,011
which is why I need more time.

504
00:24:28,120 --> 00:24:30,043
Well, then you need to convince Harvey
to let you keep going,

505
00:24:30,160 --> 00:24:31,764
because if you don't and he finds out...

506
00:24:31,880 --> 00:24:33,245
He is not gonna find out.

507
00:24:33,360 --> 00:24:35,169
Mike, he's not gonna find out from me,

508
00:24:36,320 --> 00:24:38,527
but if I've learned one thing
in the last six months

509
00:24:38,640 --> 00:24:42,690
of working here, it's that if he finds out
from somebody else,

510
00:24:42,800 --> 00:24:44,404
you're gonna regret it.

511
00:24:51,040 --> 00:24:52,530
You come here to tell me
you're taking that vacation?

512
00:24:52,720 --> 00:24:54,290
I came by to ask
when Mike Ross started taking

513
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:56,289
- whistle-blower cases.
- Jessica...

514
00:24:56,400 --> 00:24:59,006
I want you to put the brakes on him
before this gets out of control.

515
00:24:59,120 --> 00:25:00,690
Well, I'm not gonna do that.

516
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:02,723
- Harvey.
- Jessica, it's one case.

517
00:25:02,840 --> 00:25:05,002
He asked me to trust him,
and I'm gonna do it.

518
00:25:05,160 --> 00:25:07,401
And if you're ever gonna
be able to enjoy a vacation,

519
00:25:07,560 --> 00:25:09,005
you're gonna have to trust me.

520
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:13,127
All right. Good night.

521
00:25:13,880 --> 00:25:15,689
Bon voyage.

522
00:25:16,320 --> 00:25:18,322
You do know
that doesn't mean "good night."

523
00:25:18,440 --> 00:25:19,282
Of course I do.

524
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:21,209
Do you know how to say
"good night" in French?

525
00:25:21,680 --> 00:25:23,409
What, do you think
I'm some kind of Neanderthal?

526
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:26,328
You don't know one word
of French, do you?

527
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:30,644
- Ménage é trois.
- You're an idiot.

528
00:25:32,040 --> 00:25:33,963
Ménage é quatre.

529
00:25:34,080 --> 00:25:35,570
Ménage é cinq.

530
00:25:37,800 --> 00:25:38,926
Can I come in?

531
00:25:43,880 --> 00:25:45,484
What's going on?

532
00:25:46,640 --> 00:25:48,927
- We have a problem.
- I'm listening.

533
00:25:49,720 --> 00:25:52,530
Liberty Rail's report
directly contradicts our claim.

534
00:25:52,640 --> 00:25:55,484
- That's a big damn problem.
- I believe my client, Harvey.

535
00:25:55,640 --> 00:25:56,880
Based on what, your gut?

536
00:25:57,000 --> 00:25:58,764
No, I found the guy
who wrote the report.

537
00:25:58,880 --> 00:26:02,885
He's on indefinite leave in Australia,
where we can't subpoena him.

538
00:26:03,040 --> 00:26:06,249
- So it's our word against theirs.
- Which is why I'm here.

539
00:26:08,640 --> 00:26:11,723
Joe Henderson made four other
claims in the last six years.

540
00:26:11,920 --> 00:26:13,160
- You're shitting me.
- Harvey...

541
00:26:13,280 --> 00:26:14,361
That's it. I'm pulling the plug.

542
00:26:15,280 --> 00:26:16,566
I knew it.

543
00:26:16,760 --> 00:26:19,411
I knew you would bail on me the second
this thing hit the smallest bump.

544
00:26:19,520 --> 00:26:22,842
Bail on you? I backed you
because you told me you had a case.

545
00:26:22,960 --> 00:26:25,440
I do have a case.
I told you they got to this guy.

546
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:27,369
- And you got no proof of that.
- And if this were your case,

547
00:26:27,560 --> 00:26:29,642
you would be begging me
for help to get it.

548
00:26:29,760 --> 00:26:32,764
It's not my case. It's yours.
And now you're asking a jury

549
00:26:32,880 --> 00:26:35,008
to believe these guys fabricated a report

550
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:37,282
based on the word
of a career whistle-blower.

551
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:40,529
- No, I'm asking you to believe it.
- It doesn't matter what I believe.

552
00:26:40,680 --> 00:26:43,524
This guy is a goddamn shakedown artist,
and I'm pulling the plug.

553
00:26:43,640 --> 00:26:47,247
I don't care what he is.
I'm not a goddamn shakedown artist!

554
00:26:48,200 --> 00:26:49,406
- Mike...
- Harvey,

555
00:26:51,960 --> 00:26:54,167
you told me that those people
weren't my parents,

556
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:55,964
but they are
somebody's parents.

557
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:00,411
Please.

558
00:27:02,160 --> 00:27:03,446
You got 24 hours.

559
00:27:22,680 --> 00:27:24,967
You know it's against the law
to litter, don't you?

560
00:27:25,120 --> 00:27:27,726
- What do you want, Donna?
- I know you went to see Harvey.

561
00:27:27,840 --> 00:27:30,571
- You know that he wants me to fail.
- That's not true.

562
00:27:30,680 --> 00:27:32,489
I don't have anything,
and he only gave me a day.

563
00:27:32,600 --> 00:27:35,080
And if he wanted you to fail, he wouldn't
have given you another second.

564
00:27:35,280 --> 00:27:36,247
(SCOFFS)

565
00:27:36,520 --> 00:27:38,761
You know he thinks
this is about my parents, right?

566
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:43,127
Is it?

567
00:27:47,960 --> 00:27:49,689
Maybe it is,

568
00:27:50,760 --> 00:27:52,808
but what these people did
is a million times worse

569
00:27:52,920 --> 00:27:55,127
because they knew
it could happen.

570
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:56,730
Wait a second.
They knew this could happen,

571
00:27:56,840 --> 00:27:57,887
and they didn't fix it before?

572
00:27:58,000 --> 00:28:00,002
Yeah, Donna, and then they...
They rolled the dice.

573
00:28:00,120 --> 00:28:01,201
Well, what about now?

574
00:28:01,360 --> 00:28:02,407
Are those trains still messed up?

575
00:28:02,520 --> 00:28:03,806
Because that would
make them monsters.

576
00:28:03,920 --> 00:28:05,729
They are monsters,
but that would also make them idiots,

577
00:28:05,840 --> 00:28:06,807
and they're not idiots.

578
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:07,967
Well, what are you talking about?

579
00:28:08,120 --> 00:28:09,565
Well, they must have
fixed the sensors by now,

580
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:11,364
otherwise if it happened again,
they'd all go to jail.

581
00:28:11,480 --> 00:28:13,005
Well, if they fixed the sensors,
then there has to be

582
00:28:13,120 --> 00:28:14,167
- a paper trail.
- Of course there is.

583
00:28:14,280 --> 00:28:15,805
Then all you have to do is get it.

584
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:17,889
What do you think I've been trying
to figure out all night?

585
00:28:18,040 --> 00:28:19,929
What's to figure out?
Subpoena it.

586
00:28:20,040 --> 00:28:22,930
Yeah, there's only one problem.
Harvey only gave me 24 hours.

587
00:28:23,040 --> 00:28:25,520
But now that you've come up with this,
maybe Harvey will change his mind.

588
00:28:25,680 --> 00:28:27,887
Donna, I have a theory that
I can't prove and an opposition

589
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:29,570
that's shown they're willing
to alter evidence.

590
00:28:29,680 --> 00:28:31,648
He's not gonna change
his mind, and you know it.

591
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:34,004
There's got to be another way.

592
00:28:34,120 --> 00:28:37,010
Donna, look, I appreciate
what you're doing,

593
00:28:37,120 --> 00:28:40,010
but unless you have this other way
in your pocket, please,

594
00:28:40,120 --> 00:28:44,648
just leave me alone and let me try
and think this thing through.

595
00:29:04,280 --> 00:29:07,648
No! I don't care what he says.
It's an active goddamn investigation,

596
00:29:07,800 --> 00:29:09,802
- and I'm not gonna stand around...
- You can't talk on that here.

597
00:29:09,920 --> 00:29:11,001
Hang on a second, Charlie.

598
00:29:11,120 --> 00:29:14,249
I'm sorry, we got off on the wrong foot.
ls your name Danielle?

599
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:16,285
That's what it says
on the plate, isn't it?

600
00:29:16,480 --> 00:29:18,289
Well, Danielle, I'm here
to pick up the documents

601
00:29:18,440 --> 00:29:20,522
I ordered an hour ago,
and if you don't give them to me

602
00:29:20,680 --> 00:29:23,286
in the next 15 seconds,
today's gonna be your last day.

603
00:29:23,400 --> 00:29:26,051
- You didn't talk to me.
- I said hold on, damn it.

604
00:29:27,280 --> 00:29:30,409
Look, I don't have time
to play "who spoke to who."

605
00:29:30,560 --> 00:29:32,801
lam up from DC because,
as it is, these documents

606
00:29:32,920 --> 00:29:34,410
weren't sent when they were promised.

607
00:29:34,520 --> 00:29:38,047
- I'm sorry. What is it you need again?
- Oh, Jesus Christ.

608
00:29:38,160 --> 00:29:40,970
All the maintenance work orders
from the past six months.

609
00:29:41,080 --> 00:29:43,003
I can't let you have that
without authorization.

610
00:29:43,120 --> 00:29:45,088
Well, then by all means,
let's call your supervisor,

611
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:48,044
and we can tell him
how you'd rather play Farmville

612
00:29:48,160 --> 00:29:49,321
than cooperate with me.

613
00:29:53,560 --> 00:29:54,925
Who did you say you're with again?

614
00:29:55,080 --> 00:29:57,447
Have you heard of the National
Transportation Safety Board?

615
00:30:01,640 --> 00:30:03,165
They'll give you
what you need in the back.

616
00:30:07,200 --> 00:30:08,201
(DOOR BUZZES)

617
00:30:20,880 --> 00:30:21,847
What did you do?

618
00:30:22,440 --> 00:30:24,249
- I didn't do anything.
- What did you do?

619
00:30:24,360 --> 00:30:26,966
Don't give me that.
This makes my entire case.

620
00:30:27,080 --> 00:30:29,321
But I can't use it if
I don't know where it came from.

621
00:30:29,480 --> 00:30:31,403
Oh, that looks like
it came from Liberty Rail.

622
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:36,003
Oh, oh, yeah, it just happened to walk
itself over from their secure facility.

623
00:30:36,120 --> 00:30:37,963
Well, it's possible that
somebody went over there

624
00:30:38,080 --> 00:30:39,969
and released it
from their secure facility.

625
00:30:40,080 --> 00:30:42,526
Donna, if I go to Harvey
with this and tell him

626
00:30:42,640 --> 00:30:45,291
- what I know happened, he...
- You don't know. You think.

627
00:30:45,400 --> 00:30:48,324
Don't lawyer me.
He'll never let me use it.

628
00:30:48,440 --> 00:30:50,602
Well, then don't tell him
what you think happened,

629
00:30:50,720 --> 00:30:52,848
because if you do,
he'll make you drop the case.

630
00:30:53,960 --> 00:30:56,406
Okay, right now,
I don't care about the case.

631
00:30:58,160 --> 00:31:02,165
- I care about you.
- Mike, I didn't steal anything.

632
00:31:03,440 --> 00:31:05,329
I talked my way in,
and that's what happened.

633
00:31:05,440 --> 00:31:07,681
Did you tell them this was discovery
for a case against them?

634
00:31:07,880 --> 00:31:09,962
- No.
- Then it's not admissible in court.

635
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:13,761
Well, then you have to figure out a way
to use it not in court.

636
00:31:14,640 --> 00:31:17,166
But don't ask me for my help on that.
I have done enough.

637
00:31:29,320 --> 00:31:30,401
Hey.

638
00:31:30,760 --> 00:31:32,205
Heard you wanted to see me.

639
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:35,247
I take it you patched
things up with Louis Litt.

640
00:31:35,360 --> 00:31:36,327
How do you know?

641
00:31:36,440 --> 00:31:40,206
Oh, he wanted to know if you were a
sports bar guy or a wine bar guy.

642
00:31:40,360 --> 00:31:42,567
Did you tell him I'm more
of a strip club kind of guy?

643
00:31:42,680 --> 00:31:44,842
You really want to go
to a strip club with Louis Litt?

644
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:46,843
I don't really want to go
to a strip club with anyone.

645
00:31:48,040 --> 00:31:50,088
But I do have a meeting in 10 minutes,
and it's 15 minutes away.

646
00:31:50,200 --> 00:31:51,281
Oh, I just wanted to tell you

647
00:31:51,400 --> 00:31:53,880
that I appreciate you
patching things up with him.

648
00:31:54,040 --> 00:31:55,530
There's no need to thank me.

649
00:31:55,680 --> 00:31:57,648
I would do anything
for the woman that I love.

650
00:32:00,720 --> 00:32:02,643
Even get a drink with Louis Litt.

651
00:32:11,120 --> 00:32:12,121
(MIKE CLEARS THROAT)

652
00:32:14,200 --> 00:32:16,168
You here to talk
about Anderton Software?

653
00:32:16,280 --> 00:32:18,647
Because your 24-hour
Liberty Rail pass is up.

654
00:32:18,760 --> 00:32:21,684
Then I guess it's a good thing
that just came in the mail for me.

655
00:32:21,800 --> 00:32:23,802
- What is it?
- Maintenance records showing

656
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:25,684
they replaced the heat sensors
on all of their trains

657
00:32:25,800 --> 00:32:28,326
within six weeks
after the derailment.

658
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:31,125
Now, why would they do that
if they never failed a safety test?

659
00:32:31,240 --> 00:32:32,082
They wouldn't.

660
00:32:32,200 --> 00:32:33,690
Which means Joe Henderson
was telling the truth.

661
00:32:33,800 --> 00:32:36,406
I can think of three different ways
they'll explain this away.

662
00:32:36,520 --> 00:32:39,126
Not if we can get them on record
before they know we have it.

663
00:32:40,920 --> 00:32:42,251
And why don't they know we have it?

664
00:32:42,560 --> 00:32:45,086
The same way I didn't know they got
Joe Henderson's sealed records.

665
00:32:45,200 --> 00:32:46,611
Which means you did
something sketchy.

666
00:32:46,720 --> 00:32:48,404
Harvey, do you want to spend all night

667
00:32:48,520 --> 00:32:50,443
asking me exactly
what I did or did not do,

668
00:32:50,560 --> 00:32:52,562
or do you want
to help me right a wrong?

669
00:32:55,200 --> 00:32:56,884
Donna?

670
00:32:58,640 --> 00:33:00,369
Set a deposition with Liberty Rail,

671
00:33:00,480 --> 00:33:03,563
and tell them this time
it won't just be Mike.

672
00:33:03,720 --> 00:33:04,926
I'm on it.

673
00:33:15,480 --> 00:33:16,766
Who the hell is that?

674
00:33:17,920 --> 00:33:19,524
That's the CEO of Liberty Rail.

675
00:33:19,680 --> 00:33:21,728
Yeah, I know who he is.
Who is she?

676
00:33:21,840 --> 00:33:23,251
That's their lawyer.

677
00:33:23,360 --> 00:33:26,569
- Why didn't you tell me she was hot?
- Because it's not relevant.

678
00:33:26,720 --> 00:33:28,165
- It is to me.
- Why?

679
00:33:28,280 --> 00:33:29,361
Because she's hot.

680
00:33:30,080 --> 00:33:32,048
You must be the infamous
Harvey Specter.

681
00:33:32,160 --> 00:33:34,401
- You must be...
- Evan Smith.

682
00:33:34,520 --> 00:33:36,329
Have to admit,
when I saw your name was Evan,

683
00:33:36,440 --> 00:33:37,521
I thought you were a man.

684
00:33:37,640 --> 00:33:39,005
And I have to admit,
when I saw your name was Harvey,

685
00:33:39,200 --> 00:33:40,440
I thought you were a man.

686
00:33:40,560 --> 00:33:42,722
- I think I'm in love.
- I think you are, too.

687
00:33:42,840 --> 00:33:44,285
Okay, can we get this over with?

688
00:33:44,440 --> 00:33:46,124
We sure can.

689
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:48,288
I don't even know how
you have any questions at all,

690
00:33:48,400 --> 00:33:50,721
- given our last meeting.
- We just have a few.

691
00:33:54,840 --> 00:33:56,251
MIKE: Mr. McIntyre,
before the derailment,

692
00:33:56,360 --> 00:33:59,364
Liberty Rail conducted tests on
the heat sensors on its trains.

693
00:33:59,480 --> 00:34:00,481
Is that correct?

694
00:34:00,640 --> 00:34:02,051
- Of course we did.
- And why was that?

695
00:34:02,200 --> 00:34:04,282
We run tests on all our systems.

696
00:34:05,520 --> 00:34:06,726
It's routine.

697
00:34:06,840 --> 00:34:08,251
And the finding of that report

698
00:34:08,440 --> 00:34:10,408
is that there were no problems
with the heat sensors.

699
00:34:10,560 --> 00:34:13,291
Are you going to just ask questions
that you already know the answers to?

700
00:34:13,400 --> 00:34:14,561
It's routine.

701
00:34:14,720 --> 00:34:16,290
There weren't any problems
with the sensors.

702
00:34:16,400 --> 00:34:19,244
And do you routinely
replace the heat sensors?

703
00:34:19,360 --> 00:34:21,966
Yes. We replace them
every five years

704
00:34:22,160 --> 00:34:24,208
as part of our regularly
scheduled maintenance.

705
00:34:24,320 --> 00:34:26,482
And when was the last regularly
scheduled maintenance?

706
00:34:26,600 --> 00:34:27,522
That would be two years ago.

707
00:34:27,640 --> 00:34:29,768
And you wouldn't fix something
that wasn't broken, right?

708
00:34:30,480 --> 00:34:32,448
(CHUCKLES)
Of course not.

709
00:34:32,920 --> 00:34:35,571
I'm not in the business
of wasting money, gentlemen.

710
00:34:35,680 --> 00:34:37,569
I'm a bit confused.

711
00:34:37,720 --> 00:34:40,121
If you're not in the business
of wasting money

712
00:34:40,240 --> 00:34:41,446
and there was nothing wrong
with those sensors,

713
00:34:41,600 --> 00:34:43,967
then why did you just
replace all of them?

714
00:34:44,120 --> 00:34:45,531
They didn't replace all of them.

715
00:34:45,640 --> 00:34:48,211
I think we'd like your client
to answer that question.

716
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:51,684
You're in a bit of a pickle, Richard.

717
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:53,529
You don't know whether to say
you did or you didn't.

718
00:34:53,640 --> 00:34:55,130
Of course, you could roll
the dice with your own life

719
00:34:55,320 --> 00:34:56,845
just like you did with other people's.

720
00:34:56,960 --> 00:34:59,850
HARVEY: The truth is, it doesn't matter,
because you already said on camera

721
00:34:59,960 --> 00:35:02,440
- you didn't replace those sensors.
- And we have these.

722
00:35:06,200 --> 00:35:07,201
(SIGHS)

723
00:35:14,080 --> 00:35:15,286
Where'd you get these?

724
00:35:15,400 --> 00:35:18,768
I'll tell you what I told Joe Henderson.
It doesn't matter where they came from.

725
00:35:18,880 --> 00:35:20,723
It just matters that they're here.

726
00:35:21,840 --> 00:35:24,730
- I need to talk to my client.
- That's a good idea.

727
00:35:24,840 --> 00:35:27,844
You should discuss how many zeros
you're gonna write on that check.

728
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:30,008
And one more thing.
You're not only gonna write a check.

729
00:35:30,160 --> 00:35:33,243
