because people died in that crash.

730
00:35:33,800 --> 00:35:36,451
- That's not how this works.
- It's how it works today.

731
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:42,802
MIKE: You're really gonna
force them to make a public admission?

732
00:35:42,920 --> 00:35:43,887
Damn right, I am.

733
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:46,526
- Who are you, Mahatma Gandhi?
- Somebody has to be.

734
00:35:46,640 --> 00:35:48,483
You were too busy
demanding a bunch of zeros.

735
00:35:48,600 --> 00:35:51,570
Well, I was just looking out for you.
Those suits don't pay for themselves.

736
00:35:51,680 --> 00:35:52,681
No, they don't.

737
00:35:52,800 --> 00:35:55,929
Mike, great job.
You really stepped it up.

738
00:35:56,040 --> 00:35:57,530
Thanks, Harvey.

739
00:35:57,640 --> 00:36:00,007
I think you might be starting
to come into your own, too.

740
00:36:08,800 --> 00:36:11,883
LOUIS: Really?
Every single game?

741
00:36:12,000 --> 00:36:14,241
No, just the playoffs.

742
00:36:14,400 --> 00:36:15,970
- Two sips?
- Two sips.

743
00:36:16,080 --> 00:36:18,321
- No more, no less.
- Any beer?

744
00:36:18,440 --> 00:36:21,967
Oh, no, not any beer.
Miller Lite.

745
00:36:23,440 --> 00:36:26,330
Miller Lite? What?
But she's a queen.

746
00:36:26,440 --> 00:36:28,408
What can I tell you?
She got it from her dad.

747
00:36:28,520 --> 00:36:30,443
Look, if the Giants are in the playoffs

748
00:36:30,560 --> 00:36:32,130
and Jessica doesn't take
two sips of Miller Lite

749
00:36:32,320 --> 00:36:34,243
after every single first down,
she thinks they're gonna lose,

750
00:36:34,400 --> 00:36:35,811
and there's no talking her out of it.

751
00:36:35,960 --> 00:36:38,008
And those happen a lot, right?
First downs?

752
00:36:38,720 --> 00:36:39,960
They sure do.

753
00:36:40,080 --> 00:36:41,570
So what is she like
when she's drunk?

754
00:36:42,440 --> 00:36:44,363
Well, that's a conversation
for another time.

755
00:36:44,480 --> 00:36:47,723
Ooh. I so feel you, bro.

756
00:36:52,880 --> 00:36:54,086
You know, I got to say, Louis,

757
00:36:55,280 --> 00:36:57,681
I almost feel bad
about pulling that prank on you.

758
00:36:58,120 --> 00:36:59,690
Don't feel bad.

759
00:37:01,080 --> 00:37:03,731
- It was a pretty good prank.
- Okay.

760
00:37:05,920 --> 00:37:06,762
One more?

761
00:37:06,880 --> 00:37:09,087
Only if you tell me more
about what Jessica's like at home.

762
00:37:09,720 --> 00:37:10,960
No, screw that, I want you to tell me

763
00:37:11,120 --> 00:37:12,929
what she was like back
when it was Pearson Hardman.

764
00:37:14,160 --> 00:37:15,525
Done!

765
00:37:15,640 --> 00:37:16,721
(mum-nus)

766
00:37:16,880 --> 00:37:17,927
. HEY-
. HEY-

767
00:37:18,040 --> 00:37:18,962
You're heading out for the night?

768
00:37:19,080 --> 00:37:20,605
In a few minutes.
Want to grab a drink?

769
00:37:20,720 --> 00:37:21,687
Celebrate?

770
00:37:21,840 --> 00:37:23,251
- I can't.
- Why not?

771
00:37:23,400 --> 00:37:26,961
Not that it's any of your concern,
but I'm having drinks with Evan Smith.

772
00:37:27,080 --> 00:37:30,129
- What? You got her number?
- No, she called me.

773
00:37:30,240 --> 00:37:31,480
Oh, she asked for your number?

774
00:37:31,640 --> 00:37:34,007
No, she didn't have to.
You gave it to her.

775
00:37:34,120 --> 00:37:35,201
It was on that subpoena.

776
00:37:35,320 --> 00:37:37,004
I know what's gonna
be on your subpoena.

777
00:37:37,120 --> 00:37:39,407
- What does that even mean?
- You know what it means.

778
00:37:39,520 --> 00:37:40,760
Sure as hell do.

779
00:37:42,760 --> 00:37:44,489
- You wanted to see me?
- I did.

780
00:37:44,600 --> 00:37:46,568
I take it you heard about Liberty Rail.

781
00:37:46,680 --> 00:37:47,841
- I did.
- See?

782
00:37:47,960 --> 00:37:50,566
No harm, no foul,
no mass exodus of clients.

783
00:37:51,080 --> 00:37:52,650
I'm glad.

784
00:37:53,080 --> 00:37:54,206
What's on your mind, Jessica?
You don't seem...

785
00:37:54,360 --> 00:37:56,601
I know you told Scottie
about Mike Ross.

786
00:38:05,120 --> 00:38:08,567
- How'd you know?
- I didn't till just now.

787
00:38:08,720 --> 00:38:10,324
- Jessica...
- I'm not mad.

788
00:38:10,440 --> 00:38:12,841
I just want to know
what made you want to tell her.

789
00:38:12,960 --> 00:38:14,325
What difference does that make?

790
00:38:14,520 --> 00:38:16,841
Because I want to tell Jeff
the truth about Mike Ross, too.

791
00:38:16,960 --> 00:38:18,450
What changed between now

792
00:38:18,560 --> 00:38:20,562
and when you fed him
that Louis bullshit?

793
00:38:20,720 --> 00:38:21,687
Nothing's changed.

794
00:38:22,440 --> 00:38:24,169
I just don't want
to lie to him anymore.

795
00:38:25,800 --> 00:38:27,484
He told you he loved you, didn't he?

796
00:38:29,400 --> 00:38:31,767
When the hell did you start
figuring shit like that out?

797
00:38:33,280 --> 00:38:36,887
- I didn't till just now.
- Then answer my question.

798
00:38:37,040 --> 00:38:38,929
What made you decide to tell Scottie?

799
00:38:39,040 --> 00:38:41,042
That's not what you really want to know.

800
00:38:42,080 --> 00:38:45,163
What you want to know
is if I wish I'd told her sooner.

801
00:38:46,080 --> 00:38:47,525
Do you?

802
00:38:50,080 --> 00:38:51,525
Yes, I do.

803
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:04,365
Hey.

804
00:39:04,520 --> 00:39:07,046
Hey, Rachel.
What can I do for you?

805
00:39:07,640 --> 00:39:10,246
I just wanted to come by
and say thank you.

806
00:39:11,480 --> 00:39:13,642
- For what?
- Oh, come on, Donna.

807
00:39:14,200 --> 00:39:16,885
Mike told me you saved the day.

808
00:39:17,280 --> 00:39:18,884
Oh, well, you know,

809
00:39:19,040 --> 00:39:20,610
after I saved those kids
from that burning building,

810
00:39:20,720 --> 00:39:22,449
I had a little extra time, so...

811
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:24,324
Well, then maybe you should
take the rest of the night off.

812
00:39:24,480 --> 00:39:25,561
And why is that?

813
00:39:25,680 --> 00:39:27,569
Because that's what
superheroes do.

814
00:39:54,000 --> 00:39:55,126
Macallan 18.

815
00:39:56,560 --> 00:39:57,891
You got great taste.

816
00:39:58,800 --> 00:40:01,565
- Surprised I called?
- Like I said, you got great taste.

817
00:40:01,680 --> 00:40:03,728
But let me be clear.
You want to talk settlement,

818
00:40:03,880 --> 00:40:05,530
I can't do it without Mike Ross.

819
00:40:05,640 --> 00:40:07,881
I'm definitely not here
to talk settlement.

820
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:11,288
Good, because there are things
I can do without him,

821
00:40:12,000 --> 00:40:13,843
exceptionally.

822
00:40:15,840 --> 00:40:20,528
- I want to show you a little video.
- What, did you dig up footage

823
00:40:20,680 --> 00:40:23,968
from my high school championship?
Because that'll make this too easy.

824
00:40:24,800 --> 00:40:26,450
Afraid not.

825
00:40:27,920 --> 00:40:31,049
That's your secretary
unlawfully gathering evidence,

826
00:40:31,160 --> 00:40:35,688
which means there will be
no settlement of any kind.

827
00:40:41,960 --> 00:40:45,931
And tomorrow, I'm sending this
to the district attorney.

828
00:40:46,040 --> 00:40:47,610
Enjoy your drink, handsome.

829
00:41:15,720 --> 00:41:16,562
Jessica.

830
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:19,924
Jeff, there's something
I need to tell you.

831
00:41:20,080 --> 00:41:21,605
There's something
I need to tell you, too.

832
00:41:24,400 --> 00:41:25,447
What's going on?

833
00:41:25,840 --> 00:41:27,888
What's going on is
I just had drinks with Louis,

834
00:41:28,000 --> 00:41:29,843
you know, as a favor to you.

835
00:41:29,960 --> 00:41:32,691
Turns out he's not so great
at holding his liquor.

836
00:41:33,480 --> 00:41:35,926
- What did he do?
- No, he didn't do anything.

837
00:41:36,280 --> 00:41:38,931
- You did.
- I don't...

838
00:41:39,040 --> 00:41:40,246
You see, we were actually bonding

839
00:41:40,360 --> 00:41:41,725
when I suddenly remembered
what he had done to you,

840
00:41:41,840 --> 00:41:46,209
and I... Well, I wanted to make sure
that no one ever did that to you again.

841
00:41:46,320 --> 00:41:49,449
So I asked him how he found out
about Daniel Hardman's embezzlement,

842
00:41:49,600 --> 00:41:52,888
and he started with the words,
"it was two years ago."

843
00:41:53,320 --> 00:41:55,971
- Jeff, I can explain.
- You can always explain,

844
00:41:56,080 --> 00:41:57,969
but that just means your whole story

845
00:41:58,080 --> 00:42:01,129
about how Louis got his name
on the door is bullshit!

846
00:42:01,240 --> 00:42:03,083
And I came here to tell you the truth.

847
00:42:03,200 --> 00:42:06,044
- More bullshit!
- Then let me tell you now.

848
00:42:06,160 --> 00:42:07,161
Don't you get it? We're past that now.

849
00:42:07,280 --> 00:42:08,884
- I don't want to know!
- Jeff...

850
00:42:09,000 --> 00:42:10,968
In fact, I never really
wanted to know, I just...

851
00:42:11,400 --> 00:42:12,925
I just wanted you to tell me.

852
00:42:13,040 --> 00:42:16,567
But now, no matter what you tell me,
I won't ever believe it's the truth.

853
00:42:17,200 --> 00:42:18,440
Jeff, let me in.

854
00:42:18,800 --> 00:42:20,245
It's over, Jessica.

